as '''Snake Boat Race''' in [[English Language|English]]. Other categories of boats which participate in various events of the race are ''Churulan Vallam'', ''Iruttukuthy Vallam'', ''Odi Vallam'', ''Veppu Vallam (Vaipu Vallam)'', ''Vadakkanody Vallam'' and ''Kochu Vallam''.\n\nIn 2019, Nehru Trophy Boat Race was also made a part of the newly constituted CBL - Champions Boat League<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/knights-warriors-to-race-in-boat-league/article29214987.ece|title=SC|date=|work=The Hindu|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> ; an IPL inspired sporting league being played by 9 teams across 12 races.\n\n==Winners==\nThe current hat-trick title for continuously winning three times in a row is held by Kumarakom Town Boat Club under the leadership of Raju Vadakkathu Kumarakom Kottayam.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"}\n|-\n! align = \"center\" bgcolor = \"#FFD700\" | Year\n! align = \"center\" bgcolor = \"#FFD700\" | Club\n! align = \"center\" bgcolor = \"#FFD700\" | Winners\n! align = \"center\" bgcolor = \"#FFD700\" | Captain\n|-\n| 1952\n|Nadubhagam Boat club\n|[[natubhagam chundan]]\n|ChakkoMappila Mattu Mappila\n|-\n|1954\n|Kavalam team\n|[[Kavalam Chundan]]\n|ThommanJoseph\n|-\n|1955\n|Nedumudi NSS Karayogam\n|[[Paarthasarathi Chundan]]\n|KG Raghavan Nair\n|-\n|1956\n|Kavalam team\n|Kavaalam chundan\n|ThommanJoseph\n|-\n|1957\n|Ponga Boat club\n|[[Neoplian Chundan]]\n|JosephCheriyan\n|-\n|1958\n|Ponga Boat club  <br> Kavalam Boat Club\n|Neoplian Chundan <br> Kavalam Chundan\n|CheriyanJoseph & T J Job\n|-\n|1959\n|Ponga Boat club\n|[[Neoplian Chundan]]\n|CheriyanVargees\n|-\n|1960\n|Kavalam boat club\n|Kavalam Chundan\n|Matthachan\n|-\n|1961\n|Ponga Boat club\n|[[Neoplian Chundan]]\n|CheriyanVargees\n|-\n|1962\n|Kavalam boat club\n|Kavaalam chundan\n|TJ Job\n|-\n|1963\n|U.B.C Kainakary\n|[[Kainakary chundan]]\n|PK Thankachan\n|-\n|1964\n|U.B.C Kainakary\n|[[St. George Chundan]]\n|PK Thankachan\n|-\n|1965\n|